    "description": "Sanden Corporation, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the development, manufacturing, and sale of automotive air conditioning systems and compressors in Japan, Europe, and internationally. It offers heat pump system products; system product components, such as compressors, HVAC units, heat exchangers, electric coolant heaters, and pipes for air conditioning. The company is also involved in provision of air conditioning systems for off highway vehicles; and intercoolers. The company was formerly known as Sanden Holdings Corporation and changed its name to Sanden Corporation in January 2022. The company was incorporated in 1943 and is headquartered in Isesaki, Japan. Sanden Corporation operates as a subsidiary of Hisense Japan Automotive Air-Conditioning Systems Corporation."
